# Architecture and domain

Comprehensive digital health ecosystem: telemedicine, appointments, e-prescriptions, labs, mental health, maternal care.

**Stack:** .NET 8 / ASP.NET Core · Clean Architecture · EF Core · PostgreSQL · MongoDB · Redis · Elasticsearch · SignalR · WebRTC (Agora/Twilio) · Hangfire · MediatR · Outbox Pattern  
**AI/ML:** Python FastAPI (HealthPlatform.AI) · FsCheck (C#) · Hypothesis (Python)

## Two deployable projects in one monorepo

- **HealthPlatform.API** → .NET 8 / ASP.NET Core (main backend — all client traffic)
- **HealthPlatform.AI** → Python FastAPI (AI/ML services — internal only, no external traffic)

## .NET project layout

- `src/HealthPlatform.Domain` → Entities, value objects, domain events, domain service interfaces, business rules
- `src/HealthPlatform.Application` → MediatR commands/queries/handlers, domain event handlers, DTOs, validator interfaces
- `src/HealthPlatform.Infrastructure` → EF Core repos, PostgreSQL/MongoDB/Redis/Elasticsearch clients, external HTTP clients, Hangfire jobs, notification delivery
- `src/HealthPlatform.API` → ASP.NET Core controllers/minimal API endpoints, SignalR hubs, auth middleware, request validation

## Python AI project layout (`services/ai/`)

- `services/ai/symptom_checker/` — Symptom triage, specialist recommendation
- `services/ai/credit_scoring/` — Payment history analysis, credit limit computation
- `services/ai/analytics/` — Dashboard aggregations, exportable reports
- `services/ai/nlp/` — Emergency keyword detection in free-text inputs

## Strict dependency rules — never violate

- **Domain** → zero external dependencies
- **Application** → depends only on Domain
- **Infrastructure** → depends on Application + Domain (implements Application interfaces)
- **API** → depends only on Application (dispatches MediatR requests; no direct DB access)
- **HealthPlatform.AI** → called only by HealthPlatform.API over internal HTTP; never receives external traffic
- Never import Infrastructure types into Application or Domain
- Never import API types into any other project

## Domain modules

Existing modules (feature folders in Application and Domain): Identity, Appointments, Telemedicine, Prescriptions, Pharmacy, Payments, Notifications, HealthRecords, Labs, Referrals, Queue, Admin, Search, Wellness, Maternal, MentalHealth, Ratings.

Never dump new features into the root Application folder — create a new module folder.

## Domain modelling

- Entities own **invariants**; use **value objects** where a concept has validation rules (e.g. dosage, currency).
- **Domain services** for rules that do not belong to a single entity; keep methods **small** and **testable**.

## Domain exceptions

Throw typed domain exceptions from domain logic — never `ArgumentException` or `InvalidOperationException`.  
Examples: `PrescriptionExpiredException`, `SlotUnavailableException`, `AccessDeniedException`, `AccountLockedException`.

## Domain events (MediatR `INotification`)

- Name pattern: `{Subject}{PastTense}DomainEvent` (e.g. `AppointmentConfirmedDomainEvent`)
- Always include: actor IDs, patient ID, timestamp, and any IDs needed by downstream handlers
- Publish via `IMediator.Publish` — never static event handlers
- All domain events are written to the DomainEvents outbox table within the same DB transaction (Outbox Pattern)
